dismissalText.commentary: Sohail Tanvir c Amla b McLaren 31 (38b 6x4 0x6 67m) SR: 81.57

commentTextItems.html: it's over! Short ball coming into Tanvir, he pulls and it's gone straight to Amla at midwicket. McLaren finished things off with Tanvir's wicket

commentPostTextItems.html: Misbah-ul-Haq: Again the same problem with us in the batting order and we couldn't change a good start into a big one, we kept losing wickets. It was an ideal start for us, but 20s and 30s are not going to win the game for us. 70s, 80s and 100s will win us the game and that's what we are missing. The target was gettable as boundaries were coming freely with the new ball, it was a matter of playing 50 overs. The ball was coming nicely on the bat. Wahab and Tanvir gave some confidence to the team with the fight there and shows the batsmen that if you apply yourselves, you can sore runs. We need to score at least 250 against a team like SA to beat them.

Faf du Plessis is the Man of the Match: It's been a tough time so I'm thankful to this performance, especially when the team wins. I've enjoyed batting up the order and hopefully I can give some more of those at No. 3. I was under massive pressure but you have to keep trying, you can never give up. I've been hitting the ball well and it's just about settling in the middle. When you get an opportunity, you cash in with a 70 or 80. I love fielding and when I always try contributing with the ball and in the field.

AB de Villiers: Very happy with our performance, we stuck to the basics and got a few partnerships going. Always easier to play with players like Amla and Steyn. We lost a couple of wickets at the wrong time but better performance today and our bowlers came to the party. We tried to limit the damage with bowling and fielding changes and tried to upset the rhythm which Shehzad was getting into. Steyn is a wonderful bowler, he's close to perfect. He brings in intensity to the team and he ups the pace of the game. Lopsy's second spell was unbelievable and Tahir's breakthroughs were really crucial and Dale brings this intensity which is irreplaceable. Faf was under pressure to perform and that's how big players perform. We want to come with the same kind of energy in the next match to win the series here itself in the next ODI.

That's all we have for you today, we'll see you for the next ODI after a day's gap on Friday. Till then, it's Vishal Dikshit signing off with the scorers Venkat Raghav and Binoy George, goodbye and good luck!

10.40pm The Wahab-Tanvir partnership showed it's not so tough to bat here and South Africa complete a clinical 68-run win to lead 2-1 now. Pakistan got off to a flier with Shehzad looking in great touch, but once Steyn got him out for 32, their middle order couldn't keep them on track for the chase. Tsotsobe's second spell stifled them further and Tahir's 4 for 53, including Misbah's wicket, virtually finished things off. Pakistan's batting concerns continue as South Africa got rid of some of their to post 259 earlier in the day.
Alex: "Quite amusing that if you look at the scorecard you'll notice that the only player to not make any real contribution today was Amla for a change. All-round team performance"

dismissalText.long: st Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi
dismissalText.commentary: Quinton de Kock st Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi 40 (57b 5x4 0x6 88m) SR: 70.17

dismissalComment.html: Afridi has struck! De Kock came down the track to a back of length delivery which was outside off, it didm;t turn and he missed it completely, easy job for Akmal as de Kock was way outside the crease. De Kock survived Ajmal and Hafeez but Afridi got him

dismissalText.long: st Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi
dismissalText.commentary: Faf du Plessis st Umar Akmal b Shahid Afridi 55 (60b 8x4 0x6 76m) SR: 91.66

dismissalComment.html: it's Afridi again and Faf's stumped too! He was coming down too often, Afridi bowled a goggly from the back of the hand which foxed Faf's drive and Akmal did the rest. Afridi has removed both the set batsmen

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c Mohammad Hafeez b Saeed Ajmal
dismissalText.commentary: AB de Villiers c Mohammad Hafeez b Saeed Ajmal 34 (40b 2x4 0x6 67m) SR: 85

dismissalComment.html: he's taken it, would you believe it! It was a poor delivery going down leg after pitching short, AB pulled and it was going over deep fine leg but Hafeez jumped backwards and got both hands to it. Pakistan are turning this one in the Powerplay

headshotImage.caption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Saeed Ajmal player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: David Miller b Saeed Ajmal 34 (33b 4x4 0x6 40m) SR: 103.03

dismissalComment.html: that one's quicker and has gone through! Pitched outside off and as it angled in, rushed through the batsman as he tried to work in on off

headshotImage.caption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jean-Paul Duminy c Misbah-ul-Haq b Sohail Tanvir 64 (88b 3x4 0x6 121m) SR: 72.72

dismissalComment.html: short and slow, Duminy waited for it to pull and managed to hit it in the air as Misbah dived forward to take a good catch at midwicket. South Africa losing momentum the here along with the wickets

dismissalText.long: c Ahmed Shehzad b Mohammad Irfan
dismissalText.commentary: Dale Steyn c Ahmed Shehzad b Mohammad Irfan 2 (4b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: another one goes - full on middle and leg, Steyn lofts it high in the air but doesn't get the distance and Ahmed Shehzad runs in from the boundary and to his right to take a good catch diving forward

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ryan McLaren lbw b Mohammad Irfan 13 (7b 1x4 1x6 9m) SR: 185.71

dismissalComment.html: appeal for lbw and the umpire raises his finger. McLaren has called for a review for this one. He shuffled across to scoop the ball fine on the leg side, missed it and the ball hit him right in front of off as it was headed for the stumps. The decision stays

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez c du Plessis b Morkel 15 (31b 3x4 0x6 47m) SR: 48.38

dismissalComment.html: drive on the up outside off, du Plessis dives forward to catch it and the umpires have having chat to check if the catch was clean or not. Du Plessis is claiming it and it's difficult to say with 100% surety from the replays if he got his fingers cleanly under the ball. The third umpire thinks it's out and Hafeez has to walk back. There wasn't any sign of the ball bouncing before du Plessis

dismissalText.commentary: Ahmed Shehzad c Amla b Steyn 32 (24b 7x4 0x6 36m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: Steyn strikes! It was a quick delivery slightly short of length outside off and shaping away, Shehzad poked at it without footwork and handed an easy catch to Amla at first slip

headshotImage.caption: Umar Amin player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Amin player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Umar Amin player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Umar Amin player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Lonwabo Tsotsobe player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Amin c de Kock b Tsotsobe 13 (27b 2x4 0x6 54m) SR: 48.14

dismissalComment.html: Big appeal for a caught behind and he's been given not out! SA want it reviewed, pitched on the channel just outside off, Amin went across to drive, there was a sound as the ball passed the bat, Illingworth wasn't so sure initially, Tsotsobe and de Kock were very confident, third umpire sends Amin back

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq lbw b Imran Tahir 19 (36b 3x4 0x6 50m) SR: 52.77

dismissalComment.html: Misbah's been given out lbw and after an eternity he reviews it, but hang on! The umpires felt that Misbah took far too long to signal the review so it's invalid now, Misbah has to go. This was the googly, lands outside off and Misbah was forward and very tentative in offering a shot, hits his thigh and Tahir was demanding in his appeal, the umpire took his time and gave him out, Misbah walked over in slow motion almost to Shafiq, discussion, too late Sir!

headshotImage.caption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Asad Shafiq player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.long: c du Plessis b Imran Tahir
dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq c du Plessis b Imran Tahir 11 (28b 1x4 0x6 40m) SR: 39.28

dismissalComment.html: Tahir strikes again! Pitched up a legspinner outside off, Shafiq drives it softly straight to du Plessis at cover for an easy peasy catch

dismissalText.commentary: Umar Akmal c & b Imran Tahir 7 (20b 0x4 0x6 25m) SR: 35

dismissalComment.html: Tahir strikes on a full toss! It was low and dipping around middle and leg on the batsman who chipped it back, Tahir had to dive to his right and he did to complete a great catch. Pakistan in deeper trouble now

headshotImage.caption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi lbw b McLaren 6 (7b 1x4 0x6 12m) SR: 85.71

dismissalComment.html: Afridi can't connect even if it's full and he's gone lbw! McLaren pitched it right up on middle, hit him right in front of middle and leg on the back foot and it couldn't have gone anywhere else. Afridi crosses the non-striker and the umpire and all of a sudden asks for a review. It was plumb and the decision stays

headshotImage.longCaption: Sohail Tanvir player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Ryan McLaren player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Sohail Tanvir c Amla b McLaren 31 (38b 6x4 0x6 67m) SR: 81.57

dismissalComment.html: it's over! Short ball coming into Tanvir, he pulls and it's gone straight to Amla at midwicket. McLaren finished things off with Tanvir's wicket

dismissalText.commentary: Wahab Riaz c de Kock b Morkel 33 (47b 3x4 1x6 44m) SR: 70.21

dismissalComment.html: he's struck straightaway! Morkel pitched it up outside off, Wahab went for a big shot and managed a thin outside edge to the keeper for an easy catch. The best partnership of the innings, worth 61, comes to an end
